# JavaFX UI Conventions

## Dialog System
- All dialogs go through `SpeleoDBModals` -- never create raw `Alert`/`Dialog` directly in controllers
- Use `createBaseAlert()` for standard alert setup (owner, modality, header)
- Use `applySimpleDialogStyle()` for the common white/shadow/header-panel styling
- Use `applyMaterialButton()` (or its convenience wrappers) for consistent button styling

## Tooltips
- All tooltips go through `SpeleoDBTooltips` -- never create raw `Popup` in controllers
- Initialize once with `SpeleoDBTooltips.initialize(stage)` during startup
- Types: `SUCCESS`, `ERROR`, `INFO`, `WARNING`

## Threading
- All UI updates MUST run on the JavaFX Application Thread via `Platform.runLater()`
- Never block the FX thread with busy-waits or synchronous network calls
- Use `PauseTransition` for delays, not `Thread.sleep` or while loops
- `SpeleoDBPlugin.executorService` for background tasks (daemon, cached thread pool)

## FXML
- Single FXML file: `/fxml/SpeleoDB.fxml`
- Controller: `SpeleoDBController` (singleton, set via `fxmlLoader.setController()`)
- `CountDownLatch fxmlInitializedLatch` guards against accessing `@FXML` fields before `initialize()`

## CSS
- Main stylesheet: `/css/fxmlmain.css`
- Style constants in `SpeleoDBConstants.STYLES`
- Material Design color palette in `STYLES.MATERIAL_COLORS`
- Never hardcode `-fx-*` style strings outside of `SpeleoDBConstants.STYLES`

## Resources
- Images: `/images/logo.png`, `/images/icons/`, `/images/success_gifs/`
- Fonts: `/fonts/Lato-*.ttf`
- Data: `countries.json`, `empty_project.tml`
